ow to implement the required RBAC. I've located the JWT verification function, and will integrate this into each route to restrict access.\n\n\n**Implementing RBAC Logic**\n\nI'm now incorporating role-based access control (RBAC) checks into my API route handlers. I've successfully implemented JWT verification, and I'm examining the decoded token to determine the user's role. My logic now includes checks for `gff_admin` for create, update, and delete operations. Initially, only `gff_admin` will be permitted for these actions. I'm focusing on the GET endpoints, deciding that even `client_admin` roles should not access all routes right away.\n\n\n**Refining Access Control**\n\nI'm now clarifying the access control strategy, deciding to simplify the initial implementation. For the MVP, I will enforce that only the `gff_admin` role is permitted to execute any write operations on `/api/v1/users`, including creation, updates, and deletion. I've re-read the task description for more clarity, and I'll revisit filtering and other access considerations later.\n\n\n"}}
