tering logic. The role-based checks for `gff_admin` and `client_admin` are straightforward. I've designed filters for `GET` requests, including role, status, client ID, and search parameters. I'm focusing on restricting `client_admin` users to only their `clientAssociation`. I've added error handling to ensure clear responses for unauthorized access. The core logic is ready!\n\n\n**Refining Filtering Logic**\n\nI've just refined the filtering logic for the user retrieval. I'm focusing on handling `client_admin` requests by the `clientAssociation` to ensure that their data access is securely limited. I've also added role, status, and client ID filters, and searching by name or email. These additional filters are added in addition to the base filter.\n\n\n**Defining POST Parameters**\n\nI'm now focusing on designing the `POST` parameters for the `/api/v1/users` route. I've outlined checks for the logged-in user's role (requiring `gff_admin`) and parsing the request body. I am now working on validating the request. The request needs to include validations for email, name, role, status, and password, as well as checking uniqueness of the email and password. I'm focusing on handling bad request errors with informative messages. I'll utilize the `getNextUserId()` function to generate a unique ID.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:50:54.437Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"2l94srt1","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/users/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { API_MOCK_USERS, verifyJwt, hashPassword, getNextUserId, MockUserDbEntry } from \"@/lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\n// Helper to authenticate and verify permissions\nfunction getAuthenticatedUser(req: Request) {\n  const authHeader = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!authHeader || !authHeader.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    return { errorStatus: 401, message: \"Missing or malformed Authorization header.\" };\n  }\n\n  const token = authHeader.substring(7);\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(token);\n\n  if (!decoded || !decoded.email) {\n    return { errorStatus: 401, message: \"Invalid or expired access token.\" };\n  }\n\n  const email = decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim();\n  const user = API_MOCK_USERS[email];\n\n  if (!user) {\n    return { errorStatus: 401, message: \"Authorized user not found.\" };\n  }\n\n  if (user.status === \"inactive\") {\n    return { errorStatus: 403, message: \"This account is inactive.\" };\n  }\n\n  return { caller: user };\n}\n\n// GET list users\nexport async function GET(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const authResult = getAuthenticatedUser(req);\n    if (authResult.errorStatus) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: authResult.errorStatus === 401 ? \"Unauthorized\" : \"Forbidden\", message: authResult.message },\n        { status: authResult.errorStatus }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const caller = authResult.caller!;\n\n    // Keep MVP simple: admin roles only are allowed to list users\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\" && caller.role !== \"client_admin\") {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied. Admin role required.\" },\n        { status: 403 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const { searchParams } = new URL(req.url);\n    const roleFilter = searchParams.get(\"role\");\n    const statusFilter = searchParams.get(\"status\");\n    const clientIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"client_id\");\n    const searchQuery = searchParams.get(\"search\");\n\n    let filteredUsers = Object.values(API_MOCK_USERS);\n\n    // Client admin can only see users inside their own clientAssociation\n    if (caller.role === \"client_admin\") {\n      const callerClient = caller.clientAssociation || \"\";\n      filteredUsers = filteredUsers.filter(user => user.clientAssociation === callerClient);\n    }\n\n    // Role filter\n    if (roleFilter) {\n      filteredUsers = filteredUsers.filter(user => user.role === roleFilter);\n    }\n\n    // Status filter\n    if (statusFilter) {\n      filteredUsers = filteredUsers.filter(user => user.status === statusFilter);\n    }\n\n    // Client filter (can match by client_id or partial clientAssociation name)\n    if (clientIdFilter) {\n      const lowerClient = clientIdFilter.toLowerCase();\n      filteredUsers = filteredUsers.filter(user => \n        user.clientAssociation?.toLowerCase().includes(lowerClient) ||\n        user.id === clientIdFilter\n      );\n    }\n\n    // Search filter (searches name or email)\n    if (searchQuery) {\n      const lowerSearch = searchQuery.toLowerCase().trim();\n      filteredUsers = filteredUsers.filter(user => \n        user.name.toLowerCase().includes(lowerSearch) || \n        user.email.toLowerCase().includes(lowerSearch)\n      );\n    }\n\n    // Exclude password hashes from the final list\n    const usersResponse = filteredUsers.map(({ passwordHash, ...user }) => user);\n\n    return NextResponse.json(\n      {\n        success: true,\n        users: usersResponse,\n        meta: {\n          total: usersResponse.length,\n          timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n        }\n      },\n      { status: 200 }\n    );\n  } catch (error: any) {\n    console.error(\"GET users error:\", error);\n    return NextResponse.json(\n      { success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\", message: \"An unexpected error occurred while listing users.\" },\n      { status: 500 }\n    );\n  }\n}\n\n// POST create user\nexport async function POST(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const authResult = getAuthenticatedUser(req);\n    if (authResult.errorStatus) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: authResult.errorStatus === 401 ? \"Unauthorized\" : \"Forbidden\", message: authResult.message },\n        { status: authResult.errorStatus }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const caller = authResult.caller!;\n\n    // Only gff_admin should create users if possible\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Only GFF platform administrators can create users.\" },\n        { status: 403 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const body = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!body) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON body.\" },\n        { status: 400 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const { name, email, role, clientAssociation, status, clearance, password } = body;\n\n    // Run backend validations\n    if (!name || typeof name !== \"string\" || name.trim().length < 2) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Name is required and must be at least 2 characters.\" },\n        { status: 400 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    if (!email || typeof email !== \"string\" || !email.includes(\"@\")) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"A valid email address is required.\" },\n        { status: 400 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const allowedRoles = [\"gff_admin\", \"client_admin\", \"client_member\"];\n    if (!role || !allowedRoles.includes(role)) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: `Role is required and must be one of: ${allowedRoles.join(\", \")}` },\n        { status: 400 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    if (!password || typeof password !== \"string\" || password.trim().length < 6) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Password is required and must be at least 6 characters.\" },\n        { status: 400 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const normalizedEmail = email.toLowerCase().trim();\n\n    // Check if user already exists\n    if (API_MOCK_USERS[normalizedEmail]) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Conflict\", message: \"A user with this email address already exists.\" },\n        { status: 409 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    // Default permissions based on the chosen role\n    let permissions: string[] = [];\n    if (role === \"gff_admin\") {\n      permissions = [\n        \"all:*\", \"read:telemetry\", \"write:telemetry\", \"read:projects\", \"write:projects\",\n        \"read:users\", \"write:users\", \"read:clients\", \"write:clients\", \"write:governance\"\n      ];\n    } else if (role === \"client_admin\") {\n      permissions = [\n        \"read:telemetry\", \"read:projects\", \"write:projects\", \"read:ai-operations\",\n        \"write:ai-operations\", \"read:documents\", \"write:documents\", \"write:support\"\n      ];\n    } else {\n      permissions = [\"read:telemetry\", \"read:projects\", \"read:ai-operations\", \"read:documents\", \"write:support\"];\n    }\n\n    const newUserId = getNextUserId();\n    const finalClientAssociation = clientAssociation || \"GFF AI Platform Core (Global Root)\";\n    const finalStatus = status === \"inactive\" ? \"inactive\" : \"active\";\n    const finalClearance = clearance || (role === \"gff_admin\" ? \"CLEARANCE LEVEL V (SECURE PLATFORM SUPERUSER)\" : \"CLEARANCE LEVEL I (BASIC VIEW-ONLY)\");\n\n    // Hash the password securely on create\n    const passwordHash = hashPassword(password);\n\n    const newUser: MockUserDbEntry = {\n      id: newUserId,\n      name: name.trim(),\n      email: normalizedEmail,\n      role: role as any,\n      clientAssociation: finalClientAssociation,\n      status: finalStatus,\n      clearance: finalClearance,\n      permissions,\n      passwordHash\n    };\n\n    // Save into the global mock database\n    API_MOCK_USERS[normalizedEmail] = newUser;\n\n    // Never return the hashed password\n    const { passwordHash: _, ...createdUser } = newUser;\n\n    return NextResponse.json(\n      {\n        success: true,\n        user: createdUser,\n        message: `User ${name} successfully created with role ${role}.`\n      },\n      { status: 201 }\n    );\n  } catch (error: any) {\n    console.error(\"POST create user error:\", error);\n    return NextResponse.json(\n      { success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\", message: \"An unexpected error occurred while creating the user.\" },\n      { status: 500 }\n    );\n  }\n}"}}}
