ser accounts, returning appropriate status codes and error messages.\n\n\n**Implementing Filtering Logic**\n\nI'm now integrating filtering for the `GET` request handler in `/app/api/v1/users/route.ts`, with checks for user roles, statuses, and client associations to refine the returned user data. I'm also adding a search functionality, filtering users by name or email. This involved processing `client_admin` filters, role filters, and inactive account filters. A search query will be used to filter by name and email. I'm focusing on ensuring data integrity with filtering.\n\n\n**Validating POST Request**\n\nI'm now implementing the `POST` request handler in `/app/api/v1/users/route.ts` to create new users. First, I'm checking authentication to see if the caller is authorized. I've added error handling to return appropriate status codes if there are authorization errors or missing/invalid fields in the request body. I'm validating the JSON body, and requiring `name`, `email`, `role`, and `password` fields. I'm normalizing the email and checking for existing users to prevent conflicts.\n\n\n**Defining User Roles**\n\nI'm now defining user roles and their associated permissions for the POST handler. I'm restricting roles to \"gff_admin\", \"client_admin\", and \"client_member\". Invalid roles trigger a 400 error. I am setting default permissions, then dynamically adjusting them based on the assigned role: `gff_admin`, `client_admin`, or a default set.\n\n\n"}}
