words, and any potential vulnerabilities in the role-based permission assignment logic. I'm also ensuring that only valid roles are processed.\n\n\n**Scrutinizing Email Update Logic**\n\nI've homed in on the email update logic within the API. I'm focusing on the email change process, meticulously analyzing the input validation and error handling, particularly around email format and uniqueness. My main goal is to fully understand how the code handles email updates, including case and whitespace handling, and the potential for conflicts. I'm also looking at the response codes to evaluate their appropriateness.\n\n\n**Analyzing Delete Logic**\n\nI'm now deep-diving into the user deletion endpoint. I've pinpointed its authorization checks, including the `getAuthCaller` and role verification for `gff_admin`, to ensure only authorized users can delete. My attention is on the logic for finding the target user, preventing self-deletion, and handling potential errors like \"Not Found\" or \"Forbidden.\" I'm also ensuring the correct error status codes are returned, and that the deletion process is clean and efficient.\n\n\n"}}
